cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper discusses ethical considerations when conducting research on online social networks (OSNs), which involves sensitive personal information. Therefore, it is likely to fall under the categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of fake identities, which relates to the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of OSNs on privacy and security, which falls under the categories of cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
